<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 06 at 2:31PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of north central Macon,
Peach, northeastern Houston, central Crawford and northeastern Taylor
Counties through 300 PM EDT...
At 231 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was near Reynolds, or 9 miles
south of Roberta, moving northeast at 30 mph.
HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Fort Valley, Warner Robins, Centerville, Byron, Reynolds, Robins Air
Force Base, Nakomis, Jack Brown Estates, Lakewood, Powerville,
Elberta, Lee Pope, Horns and Miami Valley.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.
A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM EDT for central and
west central Georgia.</instruction>
